biography.text: Öwnboss was nominated by One World Radio by Tomorrowland in their list of the 20 Most Promising Artists for 2022 and it came true. He is the artist behind the super hot track Move Your Body and one of the most streamed DJ in Brazil, his country, with more than 5 million monthly listeners on Spotify. His killer track was the world's 4th most played song of the year according to 1001 Tracklists, topping the Bass House releases on Beatport for 11 months straight. Crossing 1 billion streams across all platforms so far and being featured on the official soundtrack of EA Sports Formula 1 game, Öwnboss won the 'Best Bass House Song Of The Year' at the 2022 EDM Awards with Move Your Body. Besides his latest releases Carnival, Said & Done and Don't Kill My Vibe, Öwnboss also released amazing remixes like For An Angel (Öwnboss Remix Edit) [30th Anniversary Edition] by Paul Van Dyk, The Motto - Öwnboss Remix by Tiësto and Crazy What Love Can Do (with Becky Hill) [Öwnboss Remix] by David Guetta. His music is present in important labels and supported by many prominent artists. As far as shows are concerned, he has performed at big clubs and festivals such as Tomorrowland's Mainstage, Rock In Rio, Lollapalooza, Creamfields, Ushuaïa Ibiza, Parookaville Festival, F*** Me I'm Famous, Brooklyn Mirage, EDC Vegas and many others around the world. - Bookings: South America: contato@ownboss.com.br / North America: david.gordoni@unitedtalent.com / Worldwide: info@oneworldartists.agency /
